Cristina T
Seattle, WA173 contributions
4.0 of 5 bubbles
Tainted Beauty; let's all stop using plastic water bottles!
Apr 2019
Let's start with the bay is beautiful. I have mixed feelings about recommending it. The natural setting is spoiled by the construction and the garbage.
It is very to focus on the beauty when you see the garbage and specifically the water bottles floating around the bay. The fishermen get paid to collect garbage but obviously not enough. We saw this all over the coast of Vietnam. The beaches were clean in the morning but early afternoon the garbage appeared.
We arranged a tour of the bay and most of the boats offered similar packages with TipTop mountain (very crowded but a nice view), the caves, a visit to the pearl factory (overpriced) and a lunch. The boat was very comfortable since we were only about 16. The tour picked us at the Pier (we came on a cruise ship) and took us to the island where all the tour boats depart. There was so wait time but it was all in all pretty efficient.
When done we took a tour of Halong bay on land. Nothing to see except ugly buildings and an amusement park that I hope has seen better days. I would not recommend staying in Halong Bay overnight.
The construction in Halong bay is surreal: a lot of empty buildings waiting for the big boom of some sort. I would say just go before it is too late and it is totally taken over by mass tourism. If you have been to Phuket and wonder how it compares: I would say that Phuket was not as dramatic in terms of landscape but it was more beautiful.
Enjoy while it is enjoyable!
Written October 1, 2019
